This research is working with approximately 59278 photos from the Teenie Harris Archive. One of the goals of the research is to find patterns within the images. The first, most basic step to doing that is to see what dimensions he takes his photos in. By creating a script that collects the sizes of the photos, I created a ratio metric for each photo: width/height. When the ratio is less than 1 the photo is oriented vertically, when it is greater than 1 the photo is oriented horizontally, when it is equal to 1 the photo is square. Results:
  • The most frequent ratio was 0.79 which means most of his photos are 4:5 sized
  • The second most frequent(but significantly less frequent) ratio was 0.75 which means some of his photos are also 4:3 sized
  • 13 photos are perfectly square
  • 18546 photos are oriented vertically(31.3%)
  • 40719 photos are oriented horizontally (68.7%)
